Subtask 1
For a set of responses \(y_1, y_2, \ldots, y_n\) (variables of interest which we want to predict) and a set of corresponding predictions for those observations \(\hat{y}_1, \hat{y}_2, \ldots, \hat{y}_n\), the Root Mean Square Error (RMSE) is \[RMSE = \sqrt{\frac{1}{n} \sum_{i = 1}^n (y_i - \hat{y}_i)^2}\] Write a basic function that takes in a vector of responses and a vector of predictions and outputs the RMSE.

getRMSE &lt;- function(vec_resp, vec_pred, ...){
  MSE &lt;- mean((vec_resp - vec_pred)^2, ...)

  return(sqrt(MSE))
}

Subtask 3
Another common metric for evaluating predictions is the Mean Absolute Error (MAE) \[MAE = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{i = 1}^n |y_i - \hat{y}_i|\] So we now write a function getMAE() providing the MAE for supplied data.

getMAE &lt;- function(vec_resp, vec_pred, ...){
  return(mean(abs(vec_resp - vec_pred), ...))
}
